# Selfhost: build-compiler vs fixpoint

## Do not use interactive `cp`

```bash
/bin/cp -f SRC DST
```

Never bare `cp` when overwriting (zsh may alias `cp -iv` and hang).

## Which command?

| Goal | Command |
|------|---------|
| Refresh emitter after `src/compiler/**` edits | `python3 scripts/manager.py selfhost build-compiler` |
| ADR-029 check `sha256(s2)==sha256(s3)` | `python3 scripts/manager.py selfhost fixpoint` |
| Full s2+s3 rebuild for that gate only | `python3 scripts/manager.py selfhost fixpoint --build` |

**Default for agents:** `build-compiler` (~45–50s floor, stage-2 only).

**Forbidden for routine emitter work:**

```bash
python3 scripts/manager.py selfhost fixpoint --build --no-cache
```

Aliases of `build-compiler`: `build-s2`, `rebuild-s2` (same handler).

## Iteration discipline (important)

`build-compiler` fully recompiles the selfhost compiler. **Do not** call it
after every one-line edit — that makes the agent `45s × N` latency-bound.

1. Diagnose with the existing s2 (compile fixtures / WAT / validate).
2. Batch `src/compiler/**` edits.
3. Run **one** `build-compiler`.
4. Validate many fixtures against that s2.
5. Parallel lanes: parent rebuilds once; lanes must not each rebuild.

See `docs/compiler/bootstrap.md` → “Which command?” / “Why ~45s”.
